article.headline: Wright St 59, Wisc. Green Bay 49
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- DaShaun Wood hit all 10 of his free throws and had 20 points to lead Wright State to a 59-49 victory over Wisconsin-Green Bay on Saturday night. Jordan Pleiman had 14 points and 11 rebounds for the Raiders (11-10, 7-1 Horizon League), and Drew Burleson added 12 points. Mike Schachtner led Wisconsin-Green Bay (11-13, 5-7) with 15 points, and Ryan Evanochko had 12. Green Bay opened with a 7-0 run before Wright State went on a 7-0 run of its own, and the two played on even terms the rest of the first half until Burleson hit a 3-pointer with 43 seconds left to give Wright State a 27-24 lead at halftime. A jumper by Schachtner tied the game at 31 two minutes into the second half, but a jumper and pair of free throws by Wood gave Wright State the lead for good.
